<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1528,2023]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1528,1555]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frontal area 25% (23–26) of cranidial length, with sharp change in slope between preglabellar field and anterior border, and well-defined anterior border furrow. Seven thoracic segments. Pygidium semielliptical in outline with inflated pleural field, well-defined border furrow, and down-sloping border of even width occupying 10% (8–12) of pygidial length (sag).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
